Explanation:
1. Split the text into an array of words.
2. Create a boolean array to keep track of used letters.
3. Iterate through the broken letters and mark the corresponding positions in the usedLetters array as false.
4. Iterate through the words and count the number of words that can be typed using the broken letters.
5. Return the count.

This solution has a time complexity of O(n) because it iterates through the words and broken letters once. The space complexity is O(n) because it creates a boolean array of size n (number of words).

